1. Introduction & Career

	• Tell me about yourself. 
	• Explain your current role and responsibilities. 
	• Walk me through your DevOps experience. 
	• Explain your current project architecture. 
	• What tools have you worked with? 
	• Which tool are you most comfortable with and why? 
	• What is your day-to-day activity as a DevOps engineer? 
	• How much of your work is automation vs manual activities? 
	• What kind of environments have you supported? 
	• How many applications/microservices do you manage? 

2. Job Change / Career Questions

	• Why are you looking for a change? 
	• Why do you want to join our company? 
	• What are you looking for in your next role? 
	• What motivates you in your work? 
	• What are your career goals for the next few years? 
	• Why should we hire you? 
	• What makes you different from other candidates? 
	• What type of work environment do you prefer? 
	• Are you comfortable with on-call and production support? 
	• Are you open to learning new technologies? 

3. Project Ownership Questions

	• Explain your current project end-to-end. 
	• What was your role in the project? 
	• What major responsibilities do you own? 
	• Which parts of the infrastructure are managed by you? 
	• Which automation tasks have you implemented? 
	• What improvements have you brought to your project? 
	• What was the biggest technical challenge you faced? 
	• What was your biggest achievement in your current role? 
	• What changes did you introduce that improved reliability or performance? 
	• How do you measure success in your work? 

4. Production Support & Incident Management

	• What was your biggest production issue? 
	• Explain a critical production outage you handled. 
	• Describe your approach during a production incident. 
	• How do you prioritize issues during an outage? 
	• What steps do you follow during incident management? 
	• How do you communicate during a production issue? 
	• How do you perform root cause analysis (RCA)? 
	• How do you prevent the same issue from happening again? 
	• Have you handled a Sev-1/critical issue? Explain. 
	• How do you handle pressure during production failures? 

5. CI/CD Improvement Questions

	• Describe a time you improved a CI/CD pipeline. 
	• What problems existed before your improvement? 
	• How did you reduce pipeline execution time? 
	• How did you improve deployment reliability? 
	• Did you implement any automation in your pipeline? 
	• How did you introduce security checks into CI/CD? 
	• How did you handle failed deployments? 
	• How did your changes impact the team? 

6. Automation & Problem Solving

	• Describe a time you automated a manual process. 
	• What was the manual process? 
	• Why did you automate it? 
	• Which tools/scripts did you use? 
	• What was the benefit after automation? 
	• How do you identify automation opportunities? 
	• Tell me about a repetitive task you eliminated. 

7. Teamwork & Collaboration

	• How do you work with developers? 
	• How do you handle disagreements with developers? 
	• How do you work with QA and security teams? 
	• Have you mentored junior engineers? 
	• How do you share knowledge with your team? 
	• How do you handle someone making a mistake? 
	• How do you handle conflicts within the team? 
	• How do you manage priorities when multiple teams need support? 

8. Ownership & Leadership

	• Tell me about a time you took ownership of a problem. 
	• Describe a situation where you worked without supervision. 
	• Have you led any technical initiatives? 
	• How do you make technical decisions? 
	• How do you evaluate whether to adopt a new tool? 
	• How do you handle incomplete requirements? 
	• How do you communicate technical issues to management? 

9. Decision-Making Questions

	• A deployment is failing in production and management wants immediate rollback. What will you do? 
	• Developer wants a quick production fix without testing. How do you handle it? 
	• A team member suggests a tool you disagree with. What will you do? 
	• You have multiple critical issues at the same time. How do you prioritize? 
	• You introduced a change and it caused an outage. What will you do? 

10. Learning & Growth

	• How do you keep yourself updated with DevOps technologies? 
	• What new technology have you recently learned? 
	• What DevOps trends do you follow? 
	• Which technology do you want to improve next? 
	• How do you handle learning while managing project work? 

11. Work Style Questions

	• Are you comfortable working independently? 
	• How do you manage deadlines? 
	• How do you handle repetitive operational work? 
	• How do you document your work? 
	• How do you ensure knowledge transfer? 
	• How do you handle feedback from your manager? 
	• What are your strengths? 
	• What is one area you are improving? 
	• What kind of manager do you work best with? 
	• Where do you see yourself in 3–5 years? 

12. Final HR Questions

	• What are your salary expectations? 
	• What is your notice period? 
	• Are you interviewing with other companies? 
	• When can you join? 
	• Do you have any questions for us? 
